
SSH Hosting method of laravel


1. open putty terminal -> enter ip & port number ->after enter userName & password.
2. got to the domain work place using cd  ->  for Example cd domains/marazin.lk/public_html/verify
3. clone the project from github for example -> git clone https://github.com/Janusath/Marazin-ultimate-pos.git
			

    if you have faced any issue please generete the access token 
		how to create the access token in github? 
				1. go to setting-> Developer Setting -> Persional access tokens -> token(classic) -> Generate new token ->generete new token (classic) -> insert new token name & check the all checkbox and enter the generate token button.
				2. enter github user name and enter access token key  
4. php artisan key:generate
5. composer2 update
6. cp .env.example .env
7. nano .env

	note: if you change any value in the nano terminal 
		how to save and exit ?
			press Ctrl + O and press enter key and using Ctrl + X you can exit the terminal.


8  php artisan migrate
9. php artisan serve



			

note: if you want to remove the all folder&files please use this command->  rm -rf *
note: check the target folder path using this conmmand -> pwd
note: if you want to move the folder & file to another folder please use this command -> mv * /home/u838412098/domains/marazin.lk/public_html/verify

